social_posts.post_text: From California to Europe and points in between 2022 was a great year for travel. #travelinspiration #travelwithme #2022 #2022recap

There are times in life when a shift in perspective is what you need.  I've been fairly quiet on Instagram  the past few months.  After a record travel year I came down with Coco and have been dealing with some longer term symptoms since the end of October. High levels of anxiety,  adrenal dysautonomia ( spikes and crashes of adrenaline which I can best describe as feeling hungover), hair loss (I'm lucky I started out with a lot), difficulty focusing and heart palpitations all left me feeling like I've been hit with a bag of bricks. While the symptoms are improving (but still  there) this has left me feeling like I aged 20 years in 2 months. Exercise has always been a big part of my life and while I'm still running my pace, distance and recovery have changed a lot which was another big hit mentally.  Throughout this I've been able to keep up with my yoga practice, and not just keep up but finally accomplish a more advanced pose I've been working on for a while. That first moment of liftoff was empowering and a win I really needed right now. Even though things change in one part of life that doesn't mean you can't make progress in other ways and it's this energy I'm taking with me into 2023. #2023 #2023goals #overforty #midlifewomen #40andfabulous

"You don't act 45"

This was said to me recently from a younger friend while I was having a mini mid-life crisis.  It was clearly meant as a compliment but it got me thinking....

What is 45 supposed to act like?

I'd say more than any other decade I've experienced the life experiences of my friends are more diverse than ever.  I've got friends who are new mothers,  who are grandmothers, who are empty nesters and those like me who are child free. 

I've got friends who have climbed the corporate ladder,  who have started their own businesses, have restarted in new careers and friends who are happily running a home. 

I've got friends that have explored far corners of the globe and those that have never left home. 

My friends are engineers and authors, doctors and factory workers.

My friends can be found scaling mountains and diving in the oceans. They can also be found curled up at home with a good book and a cup of tea.

I don't know what 40 something is supposed to act like,  but I do know that just because I'm now in midlife it hasn't changed what I'm interested in and the things I like to do. What do you think about  your 40s and beyond?
#over40 #fortyandfabulous #midlifewomen

Nowhere offers up the classic seaside experience quite like Carolina Beach, NC. Whether you stroll along the Boardwalk, enjoy the sand between your toes or indulge your kids (or your inner child) with a spin on the Ferris wheel, you’ll find Carolina Beach is the quintessential beach getaway. #wilmingtonandbeaches #carolinabeach #onlyincb @wilmingtoncoast @carolinabeachnc

If you travel to eat, then @wilmingtoncoast is the place for you. Taking influence from the area’s waters and southern heritage, restaurants (including King Neptune in Wrightsville Beach) create places that feature the best coastal Carolina has to offer. #wilmingtonandbeaches #wilmingtonnc #wrightsvillebeach @wilmingtoncoast  @wrightsvillenc

Save this itinerary! No matter what kind of coastal North Carolina experience you want, @wilmingtoncoast has you covered.

Day 1-Wilmington, NC

Explore the Riverwalk.

Experience history at the Battleship NORTH CAROLINA @bb55lhc or @bellamymansion .

Dinner and cocktails at @seabirdnc or @dramyard

Day 2-Carolina Beach

Breakfast at Britt’s Donuts. (Know this is a seasonal business, but so tasty!)

Stroll the Boardwalk or relax on the beach 🏖.

Oceanfront dinner and drinks at  @oceangrillandtikibar

Day 3-Wrightsville Beach

Kayak or SUP tour with @wrightsvillesup

Dinner at @kingneptune1947 or @fishhousewb

Sunset cruise with @soundside_wb

#wilmingtonandbeaches #wilmingtonnc #wrightsvillebeach #carolinabeach @wilmingtoncoast  @wrightsvillenc @carolinabeachnc

As I have recently turned 46 I must admit some parts of midlife took me completely by surprise. Changes in hormones affected multiple facets of my health and in ways I never expected(nothing major but at a level of where it was about 30% annoying all of the time). The 27 year old in my head also had trouble reconciling  with the 46 year old in the mirror and the fact that habits that worked well between 30-45 weren't quite working anymore.  After a bit of a rollercoaster the past 6 months something seems to have settled and I feel optimistic,  energized and creative and ready to embrace this next stage of life. #midlife #fortyandfabulous

It's the first day of Octoberfest, one of the biggest parties in the world and a celebration of all things German. If you want to join in the festivities next year I have a guide for planning your first trip to Octoberfest in Munich. #munich
#oktoberfest
https://casualtravelist.com/prost-a-guide-to-visiting-oktoberfest-munich

Octoberfest is one of the biggest parties in the world and a celebration of all things German. Lace up your dirndl, Don your lederhosen and let's go ein prosit! Have you been to Octoberfest in Germany? #oktoberfest #oktoberfestmunich

Every year over 6 million people attend Oktoberfest in Munich to celebrate all things German.  Here are 5 things you should know before raising a glass.

1. Despite the name Oktoberfest actually takes place the last 2 weeks of September. 
2. Unless you want to book a table for 10 or more people you don't need a reservation! Just squeeze in wherever you find a seat and prepare to make friends.
3.There are 23 Oktoberfest tents and the large ones can hold up to 10,000 people.
4.Each brewery brews a special Oktoberfest beer  that  you can only get at the festival. The  large glasses are known as maß (pronounced mass) and hold 2 pints.
5.Make sure to bring plenty of euros as the Oktoberfest tents are cash only and be sure to tip your waitress!

#oktoberfest
#oktoberfestmunich 
#oktoberfest2023
